</strong></p><p>The show-stopping range cooker that will turn your kitchen into a showpiece.</p><p></p><p>Majestic is a freestanding statement-piece that effortlessly integrates into any space while commanding attention with its striking combination of form and function. Its design draws inspiration from the world of professional cooking and features rounded lines, crafted details, fine finishes, and solutions and technologies that are both practical and aesthetically pleasing.</p><p></p><p>Majestic range cookers are works of art in and of themselves, but they also serve as functional kitchen appliances because of the meticulous craftsmanship that goes into their curved, all-steel designs.</p><p></p><p>They are masterpieces of craftsmanship, crafted for your home's kitchen. They come in a variety of colors, including RAL Classic shades upon request, and are complemented by fine metallic finishes. They are available in a wide range of sizes, from 30 to 60 inches, and provide multiple options for installation.</p><p></p><ul><li>The indicator for residual heat</li><li>Scheduler with built-in timeout</li><li>Bridge management</li><li>Enhancement feature</li><li>Controls that slide</li><li>Preventing harm to children</li><li>Retina 4.3-inch touchscreen</li><li>Protection against overheating and liquid spills</li><li>Electronic temperature control with pinpoint accuracy</li><li>Cabinet and door soft-closing mechanism</li><li>Getting started quickly</li></ul><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Innovations in Product Technology</strong></p><p></p><p>Not only is aesthetics important, but having the best technologies available is essential for cooking well and enjoying oneself. ILVE puts its research and experience to work for you, providing solutions that guarantee the best satisfaction by combining top-level performance with maximum simplicity, safety, and user-friendliness.</p><p></p><p><strong>Technologies related to stovetops</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Dual-Platform Induction Cooktop</strong></p><p>With their modern technology and elegant design, Majestic induction cooktops (hobs) make cooking a breeze. Induction offers many benefits, such as safe cooking, reduced energy consumption, safety, adjustable temperature control, and quick cooking times, all of which make it easier to prepare dishes and recipes.</p><p></p><p><strong>Measurement of Persistent Heat</strong></p><p>Wear protective gloves and avoid touching or setting anything delicate on the glass because it is hot.</p><p></p><p><strong>Stop-Starting Timer</strong></p><p>Once the specified time has passed, the active zone is disabled.</p><p></p><p><strong>Managing Bridges</strong></p><p>If your induction cooktop (hob) has this capability, you can treat two adjacent zones as one and use a single command to control them both.</p><p></p><p><strong>Enhancement Role</strong></p><p>Makes it possible to concentrate the entire induction burner's power on a specific area, allowing you to boil and cook food more quickly.</p><p></p><p><strong>Slide Management</strong></p><p>By simply gliding your finger from side to side, you can adjust the operating temperature, for instance, thanks to this convenient \\\"touch control\\\" system.</p><p></p><p><strong>Child Protection</strong></p><p>The induction cooktop (hob) cannot be turned on using the controls once this feature has been enabled and will remain so until disabled.</p><p></p><p><strong>Preventing Liquid Spills and Overheating</strong></p><p>An automatic shutoff mechanism activates in the event of a liquid spill or overheating of the cooktop (hob).</p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>The Oven Guys</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>The Ovens: Massive Capacity and Peak Efficiency.</strong></p><p>No matter if you go with a single or double combination oven, our 36-inch range offers enough room for even the largest of dishes\\u2014its capacity is up to 4 cubic feet.</p><p></p><p><strong>Accurate Electronic Regulation of Temperature</strong></p><p>Unlike with traditional ovens, the temperature of the oven will stay consistent thanks to the electronic control.</p><p></p><p><strong>Full-Screen 4.3-Inch Display</strong></p><p>The screen guarantees excellent legibility with TFT technology, showing every function with clear and immediate graphics.</p><p></p><p><strong>Our TFT display is designed to be user-friendly, comprehensive, and high resolution.</strong></p><p>With a single touch of the big screen, you can control all the features of either the single oven or both ovens simultaneously. You can set the temperature, set the timer, and program the ovens to start and stop cooking automatically.</p><p></p><p><strong>Doors with a Gentle Closing Mechanism</strong></p><p>A shock absorber is integrated into the door hinges, allowing for a quieter and more gradual closing.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cabinet with Warming Drawer and Soft-Closing Mechanism</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>The Cooking Probe</strong></p><p>The tool you need to check the internal temperature of meat, among other things.</p><p></p><p><strong>Steam Ejection for Wet Cooking</strong></p><p>You can achieve a crispy baked dish or a soft and juicy roast thanks to this system, which removes the vapors from inside the cavity, allowing you to choose a drier or more moist cooking.</p><p></p><p><strong>Temperature ranging from 85 to 575 degrees Fahrenheit</strong></p><p>You can effortlessly and perfectly prepare even the most intricate and sophisticated recipes in an ILVE oven, whether you're proofing, cooking, roasting, or using low heat.</p><p></p><p><strong>Using High Density Insulation and Tangential Cooling Ventilation</strong></p><p>Keeps the kitchen and its furniture from getting too hot.</p><p></p><p><strong>Effortless Cleaning with the Folding Grill Coil</strong></p><p>The electric heating element of the grill can be lowered for easier cleaning of the top part of the cavity, thanks to the articulated support.</p><p></p><p><strong>Clean Enamel with Ease</strong></p><p>Because the grease doesn't adhere to the surface, it's easier to clean.</p><p></p><p><strong>Features of the Oven. UOV 80 E3 TFT S</strong></p><p></p><p></p><ul><li>The pizza party</li><li>Removing From Freeze</li><li>Cooking to extremes</li><li>A brief overview</li><li>Extremely moist cooking</li><li>Grilling with a fan</li><li>Cooking on the grill with the door closed</li><li>Aerial cuisine</li><li>Cooking with moisture from above</li><li>An Underground Kitchen</li><li>Cooking with moisture from below</li><li>Regular, static cooking</li><li>Static, moist, typical cooking</li><li>Using a number of fans to cook</li><li>Various wet fan cooking methods</li><li>Green food preparation</li></ul><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Party Pizza</strong></p><p>The lower heating element, in conjunction with the other, less powerful heating elements, produces the ideal temperature and baking conditions for pizza, bread, and focaccia.</p><p></p><p><strong>Removing From Freeze</strong></p><p>Ensures that any food that is frozen will defrost rapidly, bringing it to room temperature without changing its flavor or appearance.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking to the Extremes</strong></p><p>This steam-discharge cooker guarantees rapid and intense cooking and is ideal for foods that require a crunchy finish, such as baked potatoes and veggies, chicken, fish with a salt crust, etc.</p><p></p><p><strong>Easy Beginning</strong></p><p>Quick preheating gets the oven to the temperature you want it to be in no time at all, and then you can select the cooking mode that's going to work best with your food. When set to a low temperature, it can also defrost food quickly.</p><p></p><p><strong>Extensive Cooking with Moisture</strong></p><p>Its steam block ensures rapid and intense cooking and is ideal for moist foods such as braised meat, stewed rabbit, salt cod, and chicken cacciatore.</p><p></p><p><strong>Searing on a Fan Grill</strong></p><p>This function is great for a wide variety of foods because it is quick, deep, and uses a lot of energy. Some examples of these foods are sausages, pork or mixed kebabs, game, Roman-style gnocchi, and pork chops.</p><p></p><p><strong>Enclosure for Grilling</strong></p><p>Functions such as quick and deep grilling, browning, roasting, and cooking fillets, Florentine steaks, fish, and vegetables are highly recommended.</p><p></p><p><strong>Recipes from the Sky</strong></p><p>Burgers, pork chops, veal steaks, sole, cuttlefish, etc., all benefit from browning and the finishing touch of color that this function provides.</p><p></p><p><strong>Delicately Cooked Food from Above</strong></p><p>Excellent for browning and finishing the color of a wide variety of foods without mushiness.</p><p></p><p><strong>Lessons in Home Cooking</strong></p><p>With the exception of leavened desserts (biscuits, meringues, fruit desserts, etc.), this is the best way to finish cooking pastries.</p><p></p><p><strong>In-Depth Recipes for Moist Food</strong></p><p>In order to finish the cooking cycle with the correct amount of moisture, this is the best way to do it.</p><p></p><p><strong>Regular, Unchanging Cooking</strong></p><p>Electric ovens typically have this one setting that works well for things like roast veal, pork chops, sausages, salt cod, braised meat, game, meringues, biscuits, baked fruit, and several more.</p><p></p><p><strong>Healthy, Regular, Moist Cooking</strong></p><p>Typical static cooking gets even more wet with this.</p><p></p><p><strong>Multi-Fan Oven Utilization</strong></p><p>Lasagna, croissants and brioches, tarts, cakes, etc. can all be baked at the same time without blending aromas thanks to this feature, which also helps to save power and time.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking with Multiple Moist Fans</strong></p><p>When cooking with multiple fans, this increases the moisture content.</p><p></p><p><strong>Natural Food Preparation</strong></p><p>Slow roasting foods, like braised meats, white meats, baked pasta, and delicate pastries, necessitate longer cooking times when using the ECO function, which significantly reduces power consumption. However, this cooking cycle is not meant for foods that are frozen.</p><p></p><p><strong>Measure 65 in California</strong></p><p>Caution: Possible Cancer and Harm to Fertility</p><p><strong><a href=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/.\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">www<span>California's P65 Warnings website</span></a></strong></p></div> <div><div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/qIZ8MSDCu-Y.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">Sorry, but the video tag isn't compatible with your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/RRQlYvQPAMg.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/Uh_EEzfUhUU.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">There is a problem with the video tag in your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/wKi6ZYNcCxY.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/re1Uo4qdmcc.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">There is a problem with the video tag in your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/4JuPNm3uQqU.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">There is a problem with the video tag in your browser.</video> </div> </div></div><br/><br/><strong>Freight Charges May Apply</strong><br/><br/></div></div> </div> <h3 class=\\\"station-tabs-tabtitle\\\"><span aria-controls=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel_features\\\" aria-selected=\\\"false\\\" class=