><span>$</span>140.00</bdi></span></a></div><div><a href=\\\"/search?q=ilve+g00201\\\"><div><img loading=\\\"lazy\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/G00201_p16239-1.jpg\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE G/002/01 Stainless Steel Bain-Marie (Double Boiler) for Hot Water Bath</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>382.00</bdi></span></a></div><div><a href=\\\"/search?q=ilve+g00202\\\"><div><img loading=\\\"lazy\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/G00202_p16240-1.jpg\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE G/002/02 Steam Cooker Basins</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>452.00</bdi></span></a></div><div><a href=\\\"/search?q=ilve+g04001\\\"><div><img loading=\\\"lazy\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/G04001_p16241-1.jpg\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE G/040/01 Griddle Dome</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>245.00</bdi></span></a></div><div><a href=\\\"/search?q=ilve+g4221208\\\"><div><img loading=\\\"lazy\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/G4221208_p16378-1.jpg\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE G4221208 Scroll Claw Leg (Sold by Individual Leg) (Chrome)</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>242.00</bdi></span></a></div><div><a href=\\\"/search?q=ilve+kgset001\\\"><div><img loading=\\\"lazy\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/KGSET001_p20076.jpg\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE KGSET001 Total Extension Glide Racks</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>168.00</bdi></span></a></div></div> </div> </div> </div> \", \"Option1 Name\": \"Color\", \"Option1 Value\": \"Midnight Blue\", \"Option2 Name\": \"Trim\", \"Option2 Value\": \"Brass\", \"Option3 Name\": \"Oven Door Type\", \"Option3 Value\": \"Solid Door\"}, {\"Variant Name\": \"ILVE - 36 inch Majestic II Induction Range with 5 Elements, 3.5 cu. ft. Total Oven Capacity (Midnight Blue / Copper / Solid Door) - UMI09QNS3MBP\", \"Variant SKU\": \"UMI09QNS3MBP\", \"Variant Image\": \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI09QNS3MBP_p13629.jpg\", \"Variant All Images\": [\"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI09QNS3MBP_p13629.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI09QNS3MBP_p13629_170380.webp\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI09QNS3MBP_p13629_170381.webp\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI09QNS3MBP_p13629_170382.webp\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI09QNS3MBP_p13629_147747-1.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI09QNS3MBP_p13629_147748-1.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI09QNS3MBP_p13629_147749-1.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI09QNS3MBP_p13629_147750-1.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI09QNS3MBP_p13629_147751-1.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI09QNS3MBP_p13629_147752-1.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI09QNS3MBP_p13629_11177.jpg\"], \"Variant Price\": \"9390.00\", \"Variant Barcode\": \"8051202223416\", \"Variant URLS\": \"\", \"Variant Count\": \"\", \"Variant HTML\": \" <div aria-hidden=\\\"true\\\" aria-labelledby=\\\"station-tabs-tab_description\\\" class=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel station-tabs-default-tabpanel\\\" id=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel_description\\\" role=\\\"tabpanel\\\"> <div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"><div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"><p>The Majestic 36-inch induction range is a perfect example of how traditional Italian design can coexist with modern technology. It has a total oven capacity of 3.5 cubic feet, a 4.3-inch full-touch control display, and an enamel oven cavity that is easy to clean.</p><p>Order now for delivery in 90 to 120 days!</p><div><p><strong>Majestic</strong></p><p>The show-stopping range cooker that will turn your kitchen into a showpiece.</p><p></p><p>Majestic, a freestanding statement-piece with a style that incorporates rounded lines, crafted details, fine finishes, solutions, and technologies derived from the world of professional cooking, is a beautiful and functional fusion of form and function. It effortlessly blends into any setting while still taking center stage.</p><p></p><p>Majestic range cookers are works of art in and of themselves, but they also serve as functional kitchen appliances because of the meticulous craftsmanship that goes into their curved, all-steel designs.</p><p></p><p>Designed for your home's kitchen, these workhorses are available in a variety of colors (from 30 to 60 inches) and set-up options (from multiple options) and can be customized to RAL Classic shades upon request. They also feature fine metallic finishes.</p><p></p><ul><li>Indictor for residual heat</li><li>Automatically stops the timer</li><li>Bridge management</li><li>Function that boosts</li><li>Handles for sliding</li><li>Preventing harm to children</li><li>Retina 4.3-inch touchscreen</li><li>Fire safety and prevention of overheating</li><li>Accurate electronic regulation of temperature</li><li>Drawer and door with a gentle closing mechanism</li><li>Fast start</li></ul><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Innovations in Product Technologies</strong></p><p></p><p>Not only is aesthetics important, but having the best technologies available is essential for cooking well and enjoying oneself. ILVE puts its research and experience to work for you, providing solutions that guarantee the best satisfaction by combining top-level performance with maximum simplicity, safety, and user-friendliness.</p><p></p><p><strong>Technologies for the Kitchen Stove</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Induction Range (Oven)</strong></p><p>Using cutting-edge technology in a stylish and elegant design, Majestic induction cooktops (hobs) expedite the cooking process while minimizing the risk of burns and other food hazards. Induction also helps with cleaning, energy savings, safety, temperature control, and cooking speed, all of which are important when it comes to preparing meals and recipes.</p><p></p><p><strong>Measurement of Persistent Heat</strong></p><p>Wear protective gloves and avoid touching or setting anything delicate on the glass because it is hot.</p><p></p><p><strong>Timer with Built-In Stop Function</strong></p><p>Once the specified time has passed, the active zone is disabled.</p><p></p><p><strong>Control of Bridges</strong></p><p>With this function, induction cooktops (hobs) allow you to control two adjacent zones with one command, as if they were one big zone.</p><p></p><p><strong>Enhancement Capability</strong></p><p>Makes it possible to concentrate the entire induction burner's power on a specific area, allowing you to boil and cook food more quickly.</p><p></p><p><strong>Slide Handles</strong></p><p>For instance, you can adjust the operating temperature simply by gliding your finger from right to left or left to right thanks to this convenient \\\"touch control\\\" system.</p><p></p><p><strong>Ensuring Safety for Children</strong></p><p>The induction cooktop (hob) cannot be turned on using the controls once this feature has been enabled and will remain so until disabled.</p><p></p><p><strong>Limiting Heat and Preventing Liquid Spills</strong></p><p>A safety mechanism will activate and turn off the stovetop (hob) in the event of an overheat or liquid spill.</p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Oven Solutions</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Impressive Size and Power: The Ovens.</strong></p><p>Our 36-inch range has a capacity of up to 4 cubic feet, so you can choose between a single or double combination oven that will give you plenty of room, even for large dishes.</p><p></p><p><strong>Accurate Electronic Regulation of Temperature</strong></p><p>Unlike with traditional ovens, the temperature of the oven will stay consistent thanks to the electronic control.</p><p></p><p><strong>Full-Screen 4.3-Inch Display</strong></p><p>With TFT technology, the screen guarantees excellent legibility, showing quick and clear graphics for every function.</p><p></p><p><strong>Our TFT display is designed to be user-friendly, comprehensive, and high resolution.</strong></p><p>All the controls for the oven, including temperature, timer, and automatic start/end programming, are conveniently located on the large display, so all you need is a single finger to operate either the single oven or both ovens simultaneously.</p><p></p><p><strong>Soft Closing System for Doors</strong></p><p>A shock absorber is integrated into the door hinges, allowing for a quieter and more gradual closing.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cabinet with Warming Drawer and Soft-Closing Mechanism</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>The Cooking Probe</strong></p><p>A must-have tool for taking internal temperatures, such as those of meat slices.</p><p></p><p><strong>Steam Ejection (Hot Food Preparation)</strong></p><p>The vapors are drawn out of the cavity by this system, so you can control the moisture level during cooking, giving you crispy baked dishes or juicy roasts.</p><p></p><p><strong>Range of temperatures: 85 to 575 degrees Fahrenheit</strong></p><p>You can effortlessly and perfectly prepare even the most intricate and sophisticated recipes in an ILVE oven, whether you're proofing, cooking, roasting, or using low heat.</p><p></p><p><strong>Using High Density Insulation and Tangential Cooling Ventilation</strong></p><p>Keeps the kitchen and its furniture from getting too hot.</p><p></p><p><strong>The Ultimate Cleaning Solution: A Folding Grill Coil</strong></p><p>You can clean the top part of the cavity more easily thanks to the articulated support, which allows you to lower the electric heating element of the grill.</p><p></p><p><strong>Rinse-Free Enamel</strong></p><p>Grease is easier to remove since it does not adhere to the surface.</p><p></p><p><strong>Activities in the Oven. UOV 80 E3 TFT S</strong></p><p></p><p></p><ul><li>The pizza party</li><li>Removing from Freeze</li><li>Very intense cooking</li><li>Fast start</li><li>Extensive cooking with moisture</li><li>Grilling with a fan</li><li>Cooking on the grill with the door closed</li><li>Aerial cuisine</li><li>Steaming food cooked in the air</li><li>Using the ground up</li><li>Preparing moist food from below</li><li>Regular, static cooking</li><li>Static, moist, typical cooking</li><li>Numerous fan-assisted cooking methods</li><li>A variety of moist fan ovens</li><li>Green food preparation</li></ul><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Pizza Party</strong></p><p>Perfect for baking pizza, bread, and focaccia. The lower heating element is the primary heat source, and with the assistance of the other, less powerful heating elements, it produces the ideal conditions for this kind of cooking.</p><p></p><p><strong>Removing from Freeze</strong></p><p>Guarantees rapid thawing of any and all frozen foods, bringing them to room temperature without changing their flavor or texture.</p><p></p><p><strong>Extensive Preparation</strong></p><p>This steam-discharge cooker guarantees rapid and intense cooking and is ideal for foods that require a crunchy finish, such as baked potatoes and veggies, chicken, fish with a salt crust, etc.</p><p></p><p><strong>Easy Beginning</strong></p><p>Quick preheating gets the oven to the temperature you want it to be in no time at all, and then you can select the cooking mode that's going to work best with your food. When set to a low temperature, it can also defrost food quickly.</p><p></p><p><strong>Thoroughly Moist Cooking</strong></p><p>The steam block ensures rapid and intense cooking, making it ideal for moist foods like salt cod, stewed rabbit, braised meat, chicken cacciatore, and braised meats.</p><p></p><p><strong>Grilling with a Fan</strong></p><p>This function is great for a wide variety of foods because it is quick, deep, and uses a lot of energy. Some examples of these foods are sausages, pork or mixed kebabs, game, Roman-style gnocchi, and pork chops.</p><p></p><p><strong>Enclosure for Grilling</strong></p><p>Ideal for searing fillets, Florentine steaks, fish, and even veggies quickly and thoroughly, as well as browning and roasting meat in general.</p><p></p><p><strong>Recipes from the Sky</strong></p><p>Burgers, pork chops, veal steaks, sole, cuttlefish, etc., all benefit from browning and the finishing touch of color that this function provides.</p><p></p><p><strong>Elevated Recipes for Moist Food</strong></p><p>Excellent for browning and finishing the color of a wide variety of foods without mushiness.</p><p></p><p><strong>Lessons in Home Cooking</strong></p><p>Pastries (such as biscuits, meringues, leavened desserts, fruit desserts, and so on) are best cooked in this way to finish the cooking cycle.</p><p></p><p><strong>In-Depth Recipes for Moist Food</strong></p><p>This is the best way to finish the cooking cycle with the correct amount of moisture.</p><p></p><p><strong>Regular, Unchanging Cooking</strong></p><p>Pork chops, sausages, salt cod, braised meat, game, roast veal, meringues, biscuits, baked fruit, etc. are all great candidates for this electric oven's classic function.</p><p></p><p><strong>Normal Cooking with Moist Static</strong></p><p>This makes traditional static cooking even more moist.</p><p></p><p><strong>Multi-Fan Oven Utilization</strong></p><p>Lasagna, croissants and brioches, tarts, cakes, etc. can all be baked at the same time without blending aromas thanks to this feature, which also helps to save power and time.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking with Multiple Moist Fans</strong></p><p>When cooking with multiple fans, this increases the moisture content.</p><p></p><p><strong>Eco-Friendly Recipients</strong></p><p>With the ECO function, cooking times adapt to slow roasting, like braised meats, white meats, baked pasta, delicate pastries, and so on. This cooking cycle is not meant for frozen foods, but it does allow for significant savings on electricity consumption.</p><p></p><p><strong>Measure 65 in California</strong></p><p>DANGER: Cancer and Harm to Fertility</p><p><strong><a href=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/.\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">the web<span>Visit P65Warnings.ca.gov for more information.</span></a></strong></p></div> <div><div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/q